                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>Describes a location by an asset that is not part of the data set but referenced within an other data set (outside the current EULYNX XML).</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LocationDescription</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#LocationOfInterest -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#LocationOfInterest">
        <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#LocationProxy"/>
        <rdfs:subClassOf>
            <owl:Restriction>
                <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://cdm.ovh/edp/EULYNX_DataPrep/Generic/Common#isLocatedAt_LocationOfInterest"/>
                <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:comment>Point of interest to the signalling system.
Often a location that is well-identifiable, e.g. as to attract attention to a dangerpoint, e.g. to the tip of a point or gauge conflict or end of platform. 
Can be used for specifying dangerpoints, end of overlap or ATP protected location, a location where speed changes.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label>LocationOfInterest</rdfs:label>
    </owl:Class>
    


